summary: LETTER FM FLORENCE LEISHMAN (WA) REGARDING AN AUTOMATIC LOCKING PROBLEM WITH THE TRUNK OF HER 1990 CADILLAC. REPLY TO FLORENCE LEISHMAN. MS. FLORENCE LEISHMAN HAD HER HANDS INJURED ON DECEMBER 23, 2002 WHEN HER FINGERS WERE TRAPPED IN THE TRUNK OF THE CAR AND AUTOMATICALLY LOCKED ON HER FINGERS. SHE HAD TO PULL HER FINGERS OUT, BREAKING  6 OF HER FINGERNAILS, AND DEVELOPED MULTIPLE CONTUSIONS TO HER FINGER NAILS AND HEMATOSIS. SHE DEVELOPED SOME RESIDUAL NUMBNESS .  *AK           *JB    *CB
